<p>Bulgarian proverbs:</p>
<ul>
<li>Hunger sees nothing but bread.</li>
<li>In every village is the grave of Christ.</li>
<li>The clean gets dirty more easily.</li>
<li>The devil knows everything except where women sharpen their knives.</li>
<li>Forests have eyes, meadows ears.</li>
<li>God&#8217;s feet are of wool; his hands are of iron.</li>
<li>One guest hates the other, and the host both.</li>
<li>Do not lie for lack of news.</li>
<li>The oversaintly saint is not pleasing even unto God.</li>
<li>Man is ever self-forgiving.</li>
<li>God does not shave &#8212; why should I?</li>
<li>A long dark night &#8212; the year.</li>
<li>Do not salt other people&#8217;s food.</li>
<li>Become a sheep and you will see the wolf.</li>
<li>The smaller saints will be the ruin of God.</li>
<li>Where there is union a bullet can swim.</li>
<li>The wife carries her husband on her face; the husband carries his wife on his linen.</li>
<li>When a wool merchant speaks of sheep he means cloth.</li>
</ul>
<p>And &#8220;God is not sinless. He created the world.&#8221;</p>
